article.description: Harald Frey scored a career-high 19 points and led five players in double figures as Montana State beat Delaware State 91-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Montana State beats Delaware State 91-66
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- Harald Frey scored a career-high 19 points and led five players in double figures as Montana State beat Delaware State 91-66 on Saturday. Frey was 6 of 10 from the field including five 3-pointers for the Bobcats (4-2). Zach Green added 16 points and led the team with 10 rebounds. Sam Neumann had 14 points and six rebounds, Joe Mvuezolo Jr. had 11 points and five rebounds and Quinton Everett chipped in 10 points. Green and Frey both sank 3-pointers as part of a 13-0 surge by Montana State to open the second period and go up 47-36 after trailing 36-34 at the break. Frey and Everett hit back-to-back 3-pointers to extend the Bobcats lead to 17 points, 76-49, with 7:49 remaining and they cruised to the win. Kavon Waller scored 17 points and grabbed five rebounds for the Hornets (1-5) who are on a five-game skid.
